on these apps, are very happy working on them.

00:15:24.950 --> 00:15:30.790
They love creating the imagery, which is a
little different from print photographs.

00:15:30.790 --> 00:15:35.850
But the photographers love it, the editors
love it, the writers love it, and the users

00:15:35.850 --> 00:15:36.850
love it.

00:15:36.850 --> 00:15:38.399
They love looking at it.

00:15:38.399 --> 00:15:39.610
So we're doing that.

00:15:39.610 --> 00:15:46.820
We have a couple of fantastic apps, the cookie
app, cupcake app, which -- a drinks app.

00:15:46.820 --> 00:15:51.010
That's a really good one, if you're -- when
you get home from work on a Friday night,

00:15:51.010 --> 00:15:52.830
that's a good one to go to for some inspiration.

00:15:52.830 --> 00:15:57.320
[ Laughter ]
&gt;&gt;Martha Stewart: And so we're doing that.

00:15:57.320 --> 00:16:03.040
We're working very hard to get across -- I
do a daily blog which reaches, oh, on average,

00:16:03.040 --> 00:16:09.560
maybe 5- or 600,000 page views a day, which,
for a blog, and one of 12 blogs in our company,

00:16:09.560 --> 00:16:11.850
is pretty good.

00:16:11.850 --> 00:16:13.830
But people get to know you.

00:16:13.830 --> 00:16:19.690
They get to understand the value of what you're
trying to set forth.

00:16:19.690 --> 00:16:20.690
And I like that.

00:16:20.690 --> 00:16:23.760
It's a personal -- My blog is a pretty personal
blog.

00:16:23.760 --> 00:16:29.751
Lots of views of snowstorms and tragedies,
and the tragedies, the broken trees, those

00:16:29.751 --> 00:16:32.290
get the most page views, the death of a dog.

00:16:32.290 --> 00:16:33.290
Oh, my gosh.

00:16:33.290 --> 00:16:36.769
You know, it's sad, but that's what happens,
people like that.

00:16:36.769 --> 00:16:39.190
They want to commiserate.

00:16:39.190 --> 00:16:47.920
But that's -- So and we are really using as
much -- even this little device, the Nook,

00:16:47.920 --> 00:16:55.240
where you just send a PDF of a magazine to
the Nook, the economics are very favorable,

00:16:55.240 --> 00:16:57.040
and I wondered, you know, how would it do?

00:16:57.040 --> 00:17:01.850
Well, actually, the Nooks are selling well,
and the subscriptions via the Nook's selling

00:17:01.850 --> 00:17:02.970
well.

00:17:02.970 --> 00:17:05.130
So we have to figure it out.

00:17:05.130 --> 00:17:07.670
Advertisers haven't figured it out yet.

00:17:07.670 --> 00:17:09.559
Publishers haven't figured it out yet.

00:17:09.559 --> 00:17:14.380
Maybe Google has answers for me today about
what's going to happen here.

00:17:14.380 --> 00:17:21.699
But it is -- we're in a very important stage
of transition right now with media especially.

00:17:21.699 --> 00:17:25.770
Where are you going to access your information
regularly?

00:17:25.770 --> 00:17:29.580
Is it going to be in that beautiful magazine
that you can open and page through?

00:17:29.580 --> 00:17:31.830
Or is it going to be on your tablet?

00:17:31.830 --> 00:17:33.820
We don't know for sure yet.

00:17:33.820 --> 00:17:35.610
But I can see sort of where it's going.

00:17:35.610 --> 00:17:38.350
&gt;&gt;Marissa Mayer: We have some exciting demos
to show you later today.

00:17:38.350 --> 00:17:41.820
But, yes, I think we're all very excited about
tablets, particularly Android tablets.

00:17:41.820 --> 00:17:45.750
&gt;&gt;Martha Stewart: Yes, and I said -- I don't
