00:23:31.049 --> 00:23:32.049
The first book I have here.

00:23:32.049 --> 00:23:33.049
So this was "entertaining," what is your first
book.

00:23:33.049 --> 00:23:34.049
&gt;&gt;Martha Stewart: Very first.

00:23:34.049 --> 00:23:35.049
&gt;&gt;Marissa Mayer: Huge best seller, inspired,
I guess, all the books that came after it.

00:23:35.049 --> 00:23:36.049
And now your new book is a revisiting of it.

00:23:36.049 --> 00:23:37.049
&gt;&gt;Martha Stewart: This one weighs a lot more,
this is, like, six and a half pounds.

00:23:37.049 --> 00:23:38.049
Yeah, it's not a sequel, because it's quite
different.

00:23:38.049 --> 00:23:39.049
The first one was actually a textbook on how
to entertain, a picture book with beautiful

00:23:39.049 --> 00:23:40.049
visuals, and a recipe book.

00:23:40.049 --> 00:23:41.049
And this book is really, I think, more cohesive.

00:23:41.049 --> 00:23:42.049
And the first book had a lot of parties that
I was catering at the time.

00:23:42.049 --> 00:23:43.049
And this one is really all personal parties.

00:23:43.049 --> 00:23:44.049
And I also had Betsy Hawes, Elizabeth Hawes,
help me write that first book.

00:23:44.049 --> 00:23:45.049
I didn't know how to write a book.

00:23:45.049 --> 00:23:46.049
I had never written a book when I wrote that
in 1982.

00:23:46.049 --> 00:23:47.049
And she was such a good teacher.

00:23:47.049 --> 00:23:48.049
That's another thing that anybody contemplating
writing or creating something like that, if

00:23:48.049 --> 00:23:49.049
you don't know how to do it, find somebody
who does know how to do it and can kind of

00:23:49.049 --> 00:23:50.049
teach you the method.

00:23:50.049 --> 00:23:51.049
That's why we go to school.

00:23:51.049 --> 00:23:52.049
I mean -- but I had taken a writing course.

00:23:52.049 --> 00:23:53.049
So I found my voice doing that book.

00:23:53.049 --> 00:23:54.049
And I was so happy that I did.

00:23:54.049 --> 00:23:55.049
And this one, I wrote every single word.

00:23:55.049 --> 00:23:56.049
And I write final text, if I can.

00:23:56.049 --> 00:23:57.049
I think about it a lot.

00:23:57.049 --> 00:23:58.049
And we took the pictures for four years.

00:23:58.049 --> 00:23:59.049
So during that time, I sort of knew what I
was going to say.

00:23:59.049 --> 00:24:00.049
And then I sat down last Christmas and took
until I finished on my third-floor craft room,

00:24:00.049 --> 00:24:01.049
and wrote away.

00:24:01.049 --> 00:24:02.049
So there it is.

00:24:02.049 --> 00:24:03.049
&gt;&gt;Marissa Mayer: And how do you decide what
to include in the book?

